cards.name: Ho-Oh
cards.description: It will reveal itself before a pure-hearted Trainer by shining its bright, rainbow-colored wings.

attacks.name: Sacred Fire
attacks.effect: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Fire Blast
attacks.effect: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.name: Blastoise
cards.description: A brutal Pokémon with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high-speed tackles.

abilities.name: Rain Dance
abilities.effect: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach 1 Water Energy card to 1 of your Water Pokémon. (This doesn't use up your 1 Energy card attachment for the turn.) This power can't be used if Blastoise is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.effect: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. Extra Water Energy after the 2nd doesn't count.

cards.name: Reshiram
cards.description: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

attacks.name: Scorching Wind
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Black Flame
attacks.effect: If Zekrom is on your Bench, this attack does 80 more damage.

cards.name: Kyogre
cards.description: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

attacks.name: Aqua Storm
attacks.effect: Discard the top 5 cards of your deck, and then choose 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage for each Energy card you discarded in this way to each of those Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.name: Palkia
cards.description: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

abilities.name: Absolute Space
abilities.effect: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't play any Stadium cards from their hand.

attacks.name: Overdrive Smash
attacks.effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Overdrive Smash attack does 80 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

cards.name: Charizard
cards.description: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to unintentionally cause forest fires.

abilities.name: Energy Burn
abilities.effect: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may turn all Energy attached to Charizard into Fire Energy for the rest of the turn. This power can't be used if Charizard is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.effect: Discard 2 Energy cards attached to Charizard in order to use this attack.

cards.name: Pikachu
cards.description: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.

attacks.name: Thunder Jolt
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Thunder Shock
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Fly
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Max Balloon
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Basic Pokémon.

cards.name: Dark Gyarados
cards.description: Normally found only in the deep ocean, it has recently been seen in shallow waters as well.

abilities.name: Final Beam
abilities.effect: When Dark Gyarados is Knocked Out by an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this power does 20 damage for each Water Energy attached to Dark Gyarados to the Pokémon that Knocked Out Dark Gyarados. Apply Weakness and Resistance. This power doesn't work if Dark Gyarados is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Ice Beam
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Max Surfer
attacks.effect: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Power Saver
abilities.effect: As long as the number of Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) that has Team Magma in its name is 3 or less, Team Magma's Groudon can't attack.

attacks.name: Linear Attack
attacks.effect: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Pulverize
attacks.effect: If the Defending Pokémon already has at least 2 damage counters on it, this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

cards.name: Zekrom
cards.description: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

attacks.name: Field Crush
attacks.effect: If your opponent has a Stadium in play, discard it.

attacks.name: White Thunder
attacks.effect: If Reshiram is on your Bench, this attack does 80 more damage.

cards.name: Mew
cards.description: Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokémon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.

abilities.name: Mysterious Tail
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 6 cards of your deck, reveal an Item card you find there, and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

cards.name: Xerneas
cards.description: When the horns on its head shine in seven different colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

attacks.name: Breath of Life
attacks.effect: Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards of different types and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.name: Cosmog
cards.description: Whether or not it's a Pokémon from this world is a mystery. When it's in a jam, it warps away to a safe place to hide.

attacks.name: Star Protection
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

cards.name: Cosmoem
cards.description: As it absorbs light, Cosmoem continues to grow. Its golden shell is surprisingly solid.

attacks.name: Star Protection
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

cards.name: Venusaur
cards.description: This plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

abilities.name: Energy Trans
abilities.effect: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may take 1 Grass Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokémon and attach it to a different one. This power can't be used if Venusaur is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

cards.name: Lunala
cards.description: It sometimes summons unknown powers and life-forms here to this world from holes that lead to other worlds.

attacks.name: Lunar Pain
attacks.effect: Double the number of damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psychic Shot
attacks.effect: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Plasma
attacks.effect: If there are any Lightning Energy cards in your discard pile, attach 1 of them to Rocket's Zapdos.

attacks.name: Electroburn
attacks.effect: Rocket's Zapdos does damage to itself equal to 10 times the number of Lightning Energy cards attached to it.

abilities.name: Cosmic Power
abilities.effect: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may choose up to 2 cards from your hand and put them on the bottom of your deck in any order. If you do, draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. This power can't be used if Claydol is affected by a Special Condition.

abilities.name: Roar of the Sword
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.

attacks.name: Storm Slash
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

abilities.name: Dark Ray
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, when you put Umbreon Star from your hand onto your Bench, you may choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

attacks.name: Feint Attack
attacks.effect: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokémon.

cards.name: Groudon
cards.description: This legendary Pokémon is said to represent the land. It went to sleep after dueling Kyogre.

attacks.name: Magma Volcano
attacks.effect: Discard the top 5 cards of your deck. This attack does 80 damage for each Energy card you discarded in this way.

abilities.name: Growl of the Shield
abilities.effect: All of your Fighting Pokémon take 20 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon VMAX (after applying Weakness and Resistance). You can't apply more than 1 Growl of the Shield Ability at a time.

cards.name: Yveltal
cards.description: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

attacks.name: Cry of Destruction
attacks.effect: Discard up to 3 Special Energy from your opponent's Pokémon.

cards.name: Cleffa
cards.description: Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

attacks.name: Eeeeeeek
attacks.effect: Shuffle your hand into your deck, then draw 7 cards.

cards.name: Dialga
cards.description: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

attacks.name: Temporal Backflow
attacks.effect: Put a card from your discard pile into your hand.

attacks.name: Metal Blast
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each Metal Energy attached to this Pokémon.

cards.name: Solgaleo
cards.description: In writings from the distant past, it's called by the name "the beast that devours the sun."

abilities.name: Rush In
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Solar Geyser
attacks.effect: Attach up to 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

cards.name: Lugia
cards.description: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

attacks.name: Aero Ball
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 damage for each Energy attached to both Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Deep Crush
attacks.effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

cards.name: Professor's Research (Professor Oak)
cards.effect: Discard your hand and draw 7 cards.

attacks.name: Birthday Surprise
attacks.effect: If it's not your birthday, this attack does 30 damage. If it is your birthday, flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 50 more damage; if tails, this attack does 30 damage.

cards.name: Professor's Research (Professor Oak)
cards.effect: Discard your hand and draw 7 cards.

cards.name: Mew
cards.description: Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokémon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.

abilities.name: Mysterious Tail
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 6 cards of your deck, reveal an Item card you find there, and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

attacks.name: X Ball
attacks.effect: Does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to this Pokémon and the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psydrive
attacks.effect: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

abilities.name: Wonder Tag
abilities.effect: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Energy Drive
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to both Active Pokémon. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

attacks.name: Tapu Cure GX
attacks.effect: Heal all damage from 2 of your Benched Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

cards.name: Shining Magikarp
cards.description: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions, but never more than seven feet.

attacks.name: Gold Scale
attacks.effect: Your opponent may draw 2 cards. Either way, you may draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Dragon Bond
attacks.effect: Search your deck for a card named Gyarados, Dark Gyarados, or Shining Gyarados. Show it to your opponent and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

cards.name: Imposter Professor Oak
cards.effect: Your opponent shuffles his or her hand into his or her deck, then draws 7 cards.

abilities.name: Δ Evolution
abilities.effect: You may play this card from your hand to evolve a Pokémon during your first turn or the turn you play that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Emerald Break
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage times the number of your Benched Pokémon.

cards.name: Rocket's Admin.
cards.effect: Each player shuffles his or her hand into his or her deck. Then, each player counts his or her Prize cards left and draws up to that many cards. (You draw your cards first.)

abilities.name: Versatile
abilities.effect: Mew ex can use the attacks of all Pokémon in play as its own. (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)

attacks.name: Power Move
attacks.effect: Search your deck for an Energy card and attach it to Mew ex. Shuffle your deck afterward. Then, you may switch Mew ex with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

abilities.name: Imprison
abilities.effect: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Gardevoir ex is your Active Pokémon, you may put an Imprison marker on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. Any Pokémon that has any Imprison markers on it can't use any Poké-Powers or Poké-Bodies. This power can't be used if Gardevoir ex is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Flame Ball
attacks.effect: You may move a Fire Energy card attached to Gardevoir ex to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Break Through
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: X Blast
attacks.effect: This Pokémon can't use X Blast during your next turn.

abilities.name: Exoskeleton
abilities.effect: Any damage done to Donphan by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Earthquake
attacks.effect: Does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Bright Look
abilities.effect: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Luxray GL LV.X from your hand onto your Active Luxray GL, you may switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Flash Impact
attacks.effect: Does 30 damage to 1 of your Pokémon, and don't apply Weakness and Resistance to this damage.

cards.name: Reshiram
cards.description: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

attacks.name: Outrage
attacks.effect: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Blue Flare
attacks.effect: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

cards.name: Zekrom
cards.description: This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.

attacks.name: Outrage
attacks.effect: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Bolt Strike
attacks.effect: This Pokémon does 40 damage to itself.

abilities.name: Healing Breath
abilities.effect: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Garchomp C LV.X from your hand onto your Active Garchomp C, you may remove all damage counters from each of your Pokémon SP.

attacks.name: Dragon Rush
attacks.effect: Discard 2 Energy attached to Garchomp C. Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Garchomp C can't use Dragon Rush during your next turn.
